Install notes:  
   1# Unzip, Unrar manually.
   2# Run setup.bat, after thats done hit Woody.exe to play.
   3# Have phun!
--

This is stupid. 

A) Why would you package it like that? It's a gargantuan pain in the arse to how to manually unpack 27 rars. 

B) There IS no setup.bat. I just looked through all 27 rar files and it is not in there.

Okay, I take back my previous comment. It works, you just need to extract the contents of all 27 rars into a new folder, then open the vace001 (which will now look like an archive if all the other files are in the same folder) and the setup.bat is in there. 

Still, a poor packaging method and bad install notes.
After unarchiving, vace.exe and running from the command line (because the bat file looked fishy) the exe is flagged as Win32.Trojan.BAT.
